d [Fe/H] in a grid-based approach, would provide internal\nuncertainties of 3% in inferred stellar radius, 6% in mass and 20% in age for\nlow-luminosity giant stars. Finally, we find red giant seismology is not\nsignificantly affected by seismic signal confusion from blending for stars with\nTmag < 12.5.\n","versions":[{"version":"v1","created":"Tue, 13 Jul 2021 03:36:44 GMT"},{"version":"v2","created":"Mon, 14 Feb 2022 22:40:45 GMT"}],"update_date":"2022-03-09"}
